# Expression output-sensitivity fixture (GH #198): derived-parameter chain.
#
# kd = 2*kbase is a ConstantExpression (derived) parameter; the global function
# dfn() = kd*A_obs references it directly, so d dfn/d kbase must include the
# derived chain ∂dfn/∂kd · ∂kd/∂kbase = A_obs·2 (plus the dynamics term through
# A_obs, since kbase is also the A->B rate constant).
begin parameters
    1 kbase 0.30
    2 kd    2.0*kbase
    3 k2    0.15
end parameters
begin species
    1 A() 100
    2 B() 0
    3 C() 0
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 2 kbase #A_to_B
    2 2 3 k2 #B_to_C
end reactions
begin groups
    1 A_obs 1
    2 BC2   2,2*3
end groups
begin functions
    1 dfn() kd*A_obs
end functions
